File: AP Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Mogadishu - The US military in Africa says it carried out an airstrike in southern Somalia that killed eight Islamic extremists at a rebel command and logistics camp, 300km southwest of Mogadishu, the capital.A US military statement said the attack happened on Sunday morning. There was no immediate comment on the airstrike from Somalia's homegrown extremist group, al-Shabaab, which is allied to al-Qaeda.Somali president Mohamed Abdullahi Mohamed confirmed the airstrike, saying that Somali and partner forces destroyed an al-Shabaab training camp near Sakow, in the Middle Juba region. He said such attacks would disrupt the group's ability to conduct new attacks within Somalia.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.